    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Well, as I did in the past with the <a href="http://nlopez.io/blog/2012/05/07/using-dropbox-to-synchronize-xcode-4-snippets/">Xcode snippets</a> I&rsquo;m going to share with everyone my <a href="http://www.sublimetext.com/">Sublime Text 3</a> <a href="https://github.com/mrmans0n/sublime-text-3-config">configuration files in GitHub</a>.</p>

<p>It&rsquo;s pretty simple, it has a pretty common dark theme (RailsCasts style) and some key maps I use all the time. Nothing worth going crazy or whatever.</p>

<p>Anyway, for the curious people, I have it available in <a href="https://github.com/mrmans0n/sublime-text-3-config">a public GitHub repository</a>.</p>
